cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC 

This paper is primarily focused on object recognition in computer vision systems, specifically Deep Convolutional Neural Networks (DCNNs). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper discusses the mechanisms and processes involved in object recognition, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also compares the performance of DCNNs to that of humans, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
